I... I...

28:54.316 --> 28:56.569
Frankie, you know,

28:56.610 --> 28:58.571
I think it was a mistake

28:58.612 --> 29:01.781
that I asked you
to come up here.

29:01.823 --> 29:03.867
Maybe the mistake was...

29:03.909 --> 29:06.245
Not asking me sooner.

29:16.422 --> 29:17.881
Baby...

29:17.923 --> 29:20.426
Frankie, hold... hold on.

29:20.467 --> 29:22.678
Mmm, mmm, mmm.

29:22.720 --> 29:24.846
What...

29:24.888 --> 29:28.684
Frankie, what are you doing?

29:28.726 --> 29:31.645
Wait. Frankie,
what are you doing?

29:31.687 --> 29:34.064
Wait. Frankie, wait.

29:34.106 --> 29:35.065
What?

29:35.107 --> 29:36.609
You're gonna rip my dress.

29:36.650 --> 29:37.776
Oh, I...

29:37.817 --> 29:39.278
It's over here.

29:39.319 --> 29:42.197
Right. Right.

29:42.239 --> 29:44.700
Do it like that.

29:44.742 --> 29:47.202
Oh, man. Mmm!

29:47.244 --> 29:50.038
Ha! Wait.
Frankie, wait!

29:50.080 --> 29:52.916
Frankie. No.

29:55.419 --> 29:57.379
Oh. Right.

29:57.421 --> 29:59.423
It hooks in the back.

30:03.594 --> 30:05.345
Thank you, god.

30:26.742 --> 30:28.952
Frankie told me
what happened the next day.

30:28.994 --> 30:31.705
But I wasn't no fool.

30:31.747 --> 30:33.707
Even ray Charles could see

30:33.749 --> 30:37.336
the two of them was like
white on rice after that.

30:37.377 --> 30:39.505
You know what I mean.

30:39.546 --> 30:41.507
Thank you, Mr. Penniman.

30:41.548 --> 30:42.716
No further questions,
your honor.

30:42.758 --> 30:45.511
Fine. Then this witness
is dismissed.

30:45.552 --> 30:47.095
Groovy!

30:47.137 --> 30:49.682
State your name and address
for the records, please.

30:49.723 --> 30:51.433
Elizabeth Waters Lymon,

30:51.475 --> 30:54.520
3639 south 22nd street,
Philadelphia.

30:57.523 --> 30:58.691
Elizabeth,

30:58.732 --> 31:01.610
when did you first
meet Frankie Lymon?

31:01.652 --> 31:03.362
In 1961.

31:03.403 --> 31:06.072
See, my first husband
had split on me and our baby,

31:06.114 --> 31:08.701
so I left Yolanda
with my mama in Philly,

31:08.742 --> 31:11.411
and I came to New York
looking for work.

31:11.453 --> 31:15.248
Well, one day I was out shopping
and I ran into Frankie.

31:15.290 --> 31:18.168
I didn't know that
he was Frankie Lymon.

31:26.051 --> 31:28.428
Yes. I'd like to see
this perfume here, please.

31:28.470 --> 31:29.555
Of course.
Just a moment.

31:29.596 --> 31:31.014
Thank you.

31:39.231 --> 31:40.440
Excuse me, miss.

31:40.482 --> 31:42.192
I need you to empty
your pockets for me.

31:42.234 --> 31:43.318
Excuse me?

31:43.360 --> 31:45.362
I've been looking
all over for you.

31:45.404 --> 31:46.988
Did you find the perfume
you've been looking for?

31:47.030 --> 31:48.281
Are you two together?

31:48.323 --> 31:51.117
Yes. This is the perfume
that mama loves.

31:51.159 --> 31:52.870
Let's not forget
the bracelet for my mother.

31:52.911 --> 31:54.705
The rest of our things
are at the counter.

31:54.747 --> 31:55.831
Let's pay for it.

31:55.873 --> 31:56.998
I'm watching you.

31:57.040 --> 31:57.999
What the hell are you doing?

31:58.041 --> 31:59.251
You should thank me, doll.

31:59.292 --> 32:00.502
For what?
I ain't done nothin'.

32:00.544 --> 32:04.590
Then what is all this?
Damn, baby.

32:04.631 --> 32:06.258
You got a nursing school?
What's this?

32:06.299 --> 32:08.385
What's your angle, huh?

32:08.427 --> 32:10.512
Hey, I don't want to see
a cute thing like you

32:10.554 --> 32:14.683
wind up in the 43rd.
It's a shithole.

32:14.725 --> 32:15.893
Hmm.

32:17.477 --> 32:18.937
Hey, what kind of a dog is that?

32:18.978 --> 32:20.355
A somma dog.

32:20.397 --> 32:21.857
A somma dog?

32:21.899 --> 32:23.983
Yeah. Somma this,
somma that.

32:24.025 --> 32:25.652
Ha ha ha! I like it.

32:25.694 --> 32:27.738
He's cute. Yeah.

32:27.780 --> 32:29.698
So you got a daughter
or something?

32:29.740 --> 32:31.700
Yeah. I got
a little girl.

32:31.742 --> 32:32.701
Yeah?

32:32.743 --> 32:33.993
Her name is Yolanda.

32:34.035 --> 32:34.994
Wow.

32:35.036 --> 32:36.496
She's eight months.

32:36.538 --> 32:38.290
Bet she's beautiful,
just like her mama.

32:38.331 --> 32:41.293
So tell me, is her
daddy still around?

32:41.334 --> 32:42.961
He told me he was a singer

32:43.002 --> 32:44.463
and gave me two tickets
to his show that night.

32:44.504 --> 32:46.381
I never been to this club.
I hear it's nice.

32:46.423 --> 32:48.383
Mickey, who is he?

32:48.425 --> 32:50.218
I don't know,
but he sure is cute.

32:50.260 --> 32:51.219
He's cute!

32:53.054 --> 32:54.723
But before I go,
I just want to say

32:54.765 --> 32:57.058
if I've offended
anyone here tonight

32:57.100 --> 32:58.727
or upset you
by anything I've said,

32:58.769 --> 33:00.562
let me address that with this...

33:00.604 --> 33:01.772
Kiss my ass.

33:10.071 --> 33:12.240
Funny man. One more time.
Redd Foxx, y'all.

33:14.993 --> 33:17.871
And now coming to the stage,
one of the all-time greats,

33:17.913 --> 33:19.748
put your hands together,
ladies and gentlemen,

33:19.790 --> 33:21.082
for Frankie Lymon!

