Bullshit! Frankie didn't
wear no open shirt.

35:04.728 --> 35:05.979
He was a class act.

35:06.021 --> 35:07.522
All right.
Your honor.

35:07.564 --> 35:09.608
You making him out
like a whore like you.

35:09.649 --> 35:10.817
You shut up!
You shut up!

35:10.859 --> 35:12.611
I'm the one telling
the story, Missy.

35:12.652 --> 35:14.821
It's an a and b conversation.

35:14.863 --> 35:15.948
Frankie was classy.

35:15.989 --> 35:17.657
Miss Taylor, quiet!

35:17.699 --> 35:19.284
That doesn't sound
like my Frankie.

35:19.325 --> 35:21.703
Sit down, miss Taylor, please.

35:21.745 --> 35:23.496
Sit down.
Sit down.

35:26.666 --> 35:29.753
All right.
Continue, miss Waters.

35:29.795 --> 35:31.129
Well...

35:31.170 --> 35:34.633
♪ You've been taken
for a ride ♪

35:34.674 --> 35:42.015
♪ And I hope you're satisfied,
you rascal you! ♪

35:48.563 --> 35:50.065
You sure my friend Paula
is gonna be all right?

35:50.107 --> 35:52.609
She'll be fine.
Come on.

35:52.651 --> 35:55.361
Whoo!
Ha ha ha!

35:55.403 --> 35:57.656
Whoo!

35:57.697 --> 35:59.032
Better get a towel.

35:59.074 --> 36:00.742
This is it.
Come on in here.

36:00.784 --> 36:03.120
Make yourself at home.
Have a seat.

36:08.374 --> 36:10.543
You know...

36:10.585 --> 36:12.754
This is normally not this messy.

36:12.796 --> 36:14.756
I stay so busy, I'm always gone,

36:14.798 --> 36:17.550
I haven't had time
to clean up the place.

36:17.592 --> 36:19.052
I thought with you being
a star and everything...

36:19.094 --> 36:21.054
You thought because I'm a singer

36:21.096 --> 36:24.474
I should have maids
and servants.

36:24.516 --> 36:26.559
Well, I don't.

36:26.601 --> 36:27.727
Sure don't.

36:29.354 --> 36:32.315
In fact, this ain't
even my place.

36:32.357 --> 36:35.234
I share it with a roommate
who's always gone.

36:35.276 --> 36:38.071
That's cool.
I'm not judging you.

36:38.113 --> 36:42.159
I think it's fine.

36:42.200 --> 36:44.077
You fine, too.

36:44.119 --> 36:46.454
Thank you.

36:46.496 --> 36:48.581
You can sing, too.

36:48.623 --> 36:50.500
Thank you again.

36:50.542 --> 36:52.919
That's Zola Taylor, huh?

36:52.961 --> 36:55.839
Yeah. She's
a good friend.

36:55.881 --> 36:58.341
Mmm. She's pretty.

37:00.802 --> 37:02.679
So, you goin' out with her?

37:02.721 --> 37:06.808
Oh, no.
See, that's old news.

37:06.850 --> 37:08.935
Mm-hmm.

37:08.977 --> 37:11.897
I just don't understand.
Why me? I'm a nobody.

37:11.938 --> 37:16.735
I'm not some big star
like miss Zola.

37:16.776 --> 37:18.778
I'm just Mickey.

37:18.820 --> 37:22.574
Maybe it's because
you're not some big star.

37:22.615 --> 37:24.283
Maybe it's because you
thought I was a nice guy

37:24.325 --> 37:26.995
before... before
you knew who I was.

37:27.037 --> 37:29.873
I still think you're nice.

37:31.958 --> 37:33.835
I think you're nice, too.

37:56.399 --> 37:57.609
Mmm. Come on.

37:57.650 --> 37:59.861
What's that?

38:51.830 --> 38:53.206
We moved in together.

38:53.248 --> 38:54.707
I know, girl.

38:54.749 --> 38:56.876
Said five minutes.
I been here five hours.

38:56.918 --> 38:58.253
Ok. Right here
by the wall.

38:58.295 --> 38:59.712
I ain't doin' this all day now.

38:59.754 --> 39:01.339
Right there.

39:01.380 --> 39:03.091
Wastin' my Saturday.

39:03.133 --> 39:04.843
Girl, I'm a little woman.

39:04.884 --> 39:06.678
I'll catch a hernia
messing with you.

39:06.719 --> 39:08.680
Girl, I'm sorry
I had you dragging

39:08.721 --> 39:10.389
this heavy thing up
here with me.

39:10.431 --> 39:12.558
I should have got
one of the fellas.

39:12.600 --> 39:14.060
It's all right.

39:14.102 --> 39:17.396
I love dragging that bad boy
up four flights of stairs

39:17.438 --> 39:20.525
just so you and your
broke-ass junkie boyfriend

39:20.566 --> 39:23.528
can be comfy-cozy.

39:23.569 --> 39:25.864
How you gonna talk
about my man like that?

39:25.905 --> 39:27.699
Come on now, Mickey.

39:27.740 --> 39:29.951
The boy got a $10-a-day habit.

39:29.993 --> 39:32.037
Where you hear that lie from?

39:32.078 --> 39:34.789
Who do you think
you're talking to?

39:34.831 --> 39:37.750
He's taking you for a ride.
Seen it happen every day.

39:37.792 --> 39:39.878
I'm from the streets.
I know what it look like.

39:39.919 --> 39:41.713
When's the last time
he had a record?

39:41.754 --> 39:43.131
He's been trying.

39:43.173 --> 39:44.924
I got a record player.
I ain't heard no records.

39:44.966 --> 39:47.177
You're too hard on him.

39:47.219 --> 39:51.514
♪ No, no,
no, no, no, no, no ♪

39:51.556 --> 39:53.516
Well, it was true.

39:53.558 --> 39:55.518
Frankie hadn't recorded
in years,

39:55.560 --> 39:57.896
and by '61, music had moved on,

39:57.937 --> 40:01.900
and Frankie's career,
it was on the downslide.

40:01.941 --> 40:03.318
How you doin'?

40:05.237 --> 40:06.738
Make sure you get
a good book, all right?

40:06.779 --> 40:08.240
Will do.

40:08.281 --> 40:09.949
Hey, Mrs. Johnson.
Tell Vernon to come see me.

40:09.991 --> 40:10.950
I will.

40:10.992 --> 40:13.245
Ahh, Mickey, sweet Mickey.

40:14.871 --> 40:17.665
Easy for us.
Up we go!

40:17.707 --> 40:20.252
Gol-ly.

40:20.293 --> 40:22.212
Now, how come you
can't do that, huh?

40:24.964 --> 40:25.924
Aww...

40:25.965 --> 40:27.259
Teach him.

40:27.300 --> 40:29.928
Hey, Frankie.

40:29.969 --> 40:32.138
Aw, baby,
it's looking good in here.

40:32.180 --> 40:34.599
Well, I still got
to paint and stuff,

40:34.640 --> 40:35.975
but it's coming along.

40:36.017 --> 40:38.061
Hey, I got something
for you, sunshine.

40:38.103 --> 40:40.897
For me?
Oh, that's so sweet.

40:40.939 --> 40:44.817
Oh, my god!

40:44.859 --> 40:47.404
Frankie, god, is it mink?

40:47.445 --> 40:49.447
Of course, it's mink.
Try it on.

40:49.488 --> 40:51.783
Help me.

40:51.824 --> 40:53.285
Wow.

40:53.326 --> 40:56.246
Nobody ever done nothing
like this for me before.

40:56.288 --> 40:58.248
I love it.

40:58.290 --> 41:00.375
I love you.

41:00.417 --> 41:03.253
Frankie told me
he was gonna give me everything.

41:03.295 --> 41:04.545
Strut your stuff.

41:04.587 --> 41:08.091
And he did.
He was so good to me.

41:08.133 --> 41:10.135
I was happier
than I had ever been.

41:10.176 --> 41:12.971
When I was with him,
he made me feel like a star.

41:13.012 --> 41:14.973
Yes! Told you
I was gonna show you things,

41:15.014 --> 41:16.515
now come on, woman!

41:16.557 --> 41:19.685
But then reality hit...

41:19.727 --> 41:21.938
Big time.

41:21.980 --> 41:23.773
Frankie's drug thing...

41:23.815 --> 41:25.775
Well, it forced me to find

41:25.817 --> 41:29.028
new and interesting
places to hide cash.

41:30.280 --> 41:32.490
Hey, Frankie.

41:32.531 --> 41:34.659
You talk to Morris
about an advance?

41:34.700 --> 41:36.244
What did he say?
Yeah.

41:36.286 --> 41:38.371
What you think?
He told me to beat it.

41:38.413 --> 41:40.873
Forget him, Frankie.
Find yourself a new label.

41:40.915 --> 41:43.460
Don't let folks
control your fate.

41:43.501 --> 41:46.129
You know, I saw on
<i>what's my line?</i>

41:46.171 --> 41:48.881
Where this guy Nietzche said,

41:48.923 --> 41:51.759
"I am the master of my fate,

41:51.801 --> 41:53.136
the captain of my soul."

41:53.178 --> 41:54.512
Do you know what that means?

41:54.553 --> 41:57.015
I don't want to hear
no bullshit about Nickiski

41:57.056 --> 41:58.516
or whoever the fuck he is.

41:58.557 --> 42:00.310
I need a gig, man!

42:00.352 --> 42:02.437
Fine. I was just trying to
say some kind words to you.

42:02.479 --> 42:05.315
Stay at roulette
and stay broke, then.

42:05.357 --> 42:06.607
Can't say nothing to you.

42:06.649 --> 42:08.985
You're always lecturing me.

42:09.027 --> 42:10.403
Damn!

42:12.405 --> 42:14.240
Look, um, I need some money.

42:14.282 --> 42:16.326
No! The rent is due
tomorrow.

42:16.368 --> 42:18.744
I'm gonna give it back
to you on time. Damn!

42:18.786 --> 42:20.746
You said that shit last month.

42:20.788 --> 42:22.040
That's why we
ain't got no phone.

42:22.081 --> 42:23.541
Don't embarrass me.

42:23.582 --> 42:25.918
I got this landlord asking
for the rent tomorrow.

42:25.960 --> 42:28.921
Frankie, what are you doing?

42:30.340 --> 42:31.632
Where the money
I gave you to hold?

42:31.674 --> 42:33.551
You ain't gave me
no money, Frankie.

42:33.592 --> 42:34.552
You hid it.

42:34.593 --> 42:36.262
No, I didn't.

42:36.304 --> 42:38.556
Frankie, this shit
has got you acting crazy.

42:38.597 --> 42:41.017
You want me to look
through stuff?

42:41.059 --> 42:42.519
Frankie, what are you doing?

42:42.560 --> 42:44.896
Want me to look for the money?

42:44.937 --> 42:46.272
Where the fuck is my money?

42:46.314 --> 42:47.899
Stop that, Frankie!

42:47.940 --> 42:50.527
That shit got you acting
like you're crazy!

42:50.568 --> 42:52.611
You fucking crazy!
Where the money at?

42:52.653 --> 42:54.531
What is wrong with you?

42:54.572 --> 42:55.948
You're what's wrong with me!

42:55.990 --> 42:57.450
You're why I can't get
off the fucking dime!

42:57.492 --> 42:58.951
Always lecturing me!

42:58.993 --> 43:02.038
I ain't done nothing!

43:02.080 --> 43:03.915
I know you got the money
somewhere around here.

43:03.956 --> 43:05.208
Acting like you crazy!

43:05.250 --> 43:06.209
You got the money!

43:06.251 --> 43:07.293
What's gotten into you?

43:07.335 --> 43:08.794
You're supposed to be my woman!

43:08.836 --> 43:10.380
What is all this shit
playing games...

43:10.422 --> 43:13.007
♪ In your eyes ♪

43:13.049 --> 43:18.388
♪ Smoke gets in your ♪

43:18.430 --> 43:21.974
♪ Eyes ♪

43:22.016 --> 43:23.351
I don't need this shit.

43:23.393 --> 43:27.021
I damn sure don't need you.
You remember that.

43:28.106 --> 43:29.899
I'm gone.

